<bodybg></bodybg>
<div id="import_page"><h1 id="Title">Import a CSV File</h1>
 <table id="list_of_errors">
   <div id="errors_explained"><ul><h3>Errors explained</h3>
     <h4><li>Error messages will look like the following:   "In Row X:  (Error message) : Found [[HEADERS]] - [Data]"</li>
       <br>
       <div id="errors_text"><li>Illegal Characters are:</li>
         <ul><li>!<br></li>   <li>$<br></li>   <li>;<br></li>   <li>\<br></li>   <li>'<br></li>   <li>"<br></li></ul>
       <ul>(The easiest fix for illegal characters: ctrl+f and search for the illegal characters, replace or delete the illegal characters as appropriate)</ul>
       <li>Headers will be displayed inside double brackets [[HEADERS]]</li>
       <li>Data inside cells will be displayed inside brackets [DATA]</li>
       <li>[] - means that the cell is empty</li>
       <li>In Row X : indicates which row the error was found in</li>
       </div>

     </h4></ul></div>
 </table>

  <div id="notice"><%= flash[:notice] %></div>
 <% @forms_import.errors.full_messages.each do |msg| %>
     <li><div id="errors"><%= msg %></div></li>
 <% end %>
 <div>

<%= form_tag '/forms_import', multipart: true do %>
    <%= file_field_tag :file, accept: '.csv', required: 'required' %>
    Sigma:
    <%= radio_button_tag :row, :cosmo_sigma %>
    Web:
    <%= radio_button_tag :row, :cosmo_web %>
    <%= submit_tag  "Import CSV File"%>

<% end %>
 </div>
</div>
<br>